{\ri30 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb0 
Doctrines of res judicata and collateral estoppel did not bar landowner\rquote s declaratory judgment action challenging city\rquote s award of parking credits to restaurant without engaging variance procedure; even though trial court denied rather than dismissed landowner\rquote s previous certiorari action challenging award of parking credit, court concluded that city\rquote s decision was not quasi-judicial and that it lacked jurisdiction, District Court of Appeal\rquote s per curiam denial of certiorari relief in second-tier certiorari was also not determination on merits, and neither court determined issue of fact or law regarding claim raised in declaratory judgment action.
\par 
}
}
}
