}\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \ql \li30 \fs20 \intbl \cell \intbl 
{\ri30 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Under the doctrine of collateral estoppel, when an issue of fact or law is actually litigated and determined by a valid and final judgment, and the determination is essential to the judgment, the determination is conclusive in a subsequent action between the parties, whether on the same or a different claim. 
}
