{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb0 
When an administrative official or agency acts in an executive or legislative capacity, the proper method of attack on the official\rquote s or agency\rquote s action is a suit in circuit court for declaratory or injunctive relief on grounds that the action taken is arbitrary, capricious, confiscatory, or violative of constitutional guarantees.
\par 
}
}
}
