{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb0 
The rule against splitting causes of action is an aspect of the doctrine of res judicata and generally provides that a party must claim and recover in one action all damages sustained or accruing from one wrongful act.
\par 
}
}
}
