{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[2]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Normally affirmative defenses such as res judicata and collateral estoppel must be raised in an answer, not in a motion to dismiss, unless the face of the complaint demonstrates the defense. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
