Bolz,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 679 So.2d at 837
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (reversing dismissal of complaint on res judicata grounds when the complaint failed to refer to the prior action and the trial court \u8220\'3fcould not consider the pleadings attached to [the] motion\u8221\'3f to dismiss).
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
However, when a complaint specifically incorporated by reference the prior proceedings such that \u8220\'3fthe trial court had before it a complete history of this litigation,\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_3926_590_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_3926_590_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*590
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 the appellate court affirmed the dismissal of the complaint based on issues of res judicata and estoppel by judgment. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=Ieb2d7e510e7511d9bde8ee3d49ead4ec&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
