}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2001466516&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_107&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_107" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Fla. Dep\rquote t of Transp. v. Juliano,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 801 So.2d 101, 107 (Fla.2001)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. For the doctrine of res judicata to apply, the ruling in the prior action must be on the merits of the claim. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I1d1ec5d40c6011d9bc18e8274af85244&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2004087242&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_1255&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_1255" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Topps,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 865 So.2d at 1255
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. This promotes the purpose underlying the doctrine of res judicata that if a party has already had the matter decided, the party has had its day in court. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 \u8220\'3fBased on principles of res judicata, a judgment on the merits will thus bar \u8216\'3fa 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
subsequent
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 action between the same parties on the same cause of action.\u8217\'3f \u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I8cb5f4ae49fb11e28a21ccb9036b2470&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2029470299&pubNum=0003926&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_3926_984&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_3926_984" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Jasser v. Saadeh,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 103 So.3d 982, 984 (Fla. 4th DCA 2012)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (quoting 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1956130327&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_505&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_505" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Youngblood v. Taylor,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 89 So.2d 503, 505 (Fla.1956)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
) (emphasis supplied by 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Jasser
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 court).
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F82038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[8]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F92038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[9]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The related doctrine of collateral estoppel, also known as estoppel by judgment or issue preclusion, \u8220\'3fbars \u8216\'3fthe parties from litigating in the second suit issues\u8212\'3fthat is to say points and questions\u8212\'3fcommon to both causes of action and which were actually adjudicated in the prior litigation.\u8217\'3f \u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=Ia6154e3a26d311da9bcc85e7f8e2f4cd&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2007304713&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_634&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_634" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Cook v. State,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 921 So.2d 631, 634 (Fla. 2d DCA 2005)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (quoting 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I6730b7d80c8511d98220e6fa99ecd085&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1995101504&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_919&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_919" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Stogniew v. McQueen,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 656 So.2d 917, 919 (Fla.1995)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
). \u8220\'3fWhen an issue of fact or law is actually litigated and determined by a valid and final judgment, and the determination is essential to the judgment, the determination is conclusive in a subsequent action between the parties, whether on the same or a different claim.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (quoting 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=0291285778&pubNum=0101581&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=TS&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Restatement (Second) of Judgments
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 \u167\'3f 27 (1982)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
); 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
see also 
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I2d08403b4e2a11dbb0d3b726c66cf290&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2010367860&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_1243&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_1243" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Atl. Shores Resort, LLC v. 507 S. St. Corp.,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 937 So.2d 1239, 1243\u8211\'3f44 (Fla. 3d DCA 2006)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (determining that collateral estoppel applied when the party had made the same objections regarding a height restriction and the issue had been decided by the architectural review commission and on appeal to the special master). For collateral estoppel to apply here, the circuit court in the certiorari proceeding had to make an actual determination essential to its decision that Neapolitan is asserting in the present action.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F102038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[10]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The circuit court\rquote s order on first-tier certiorari review was not a decision on the merits. An order dismissing a case for lack of jurisdiction is not on the merits. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1995156392&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_649&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_649" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Parkway Bank v. Fort Myers Armature Works,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 658 So.2d 646, 649 n. 3 (Fla. 2d DCA 1995)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (explaining the distinction between the dismissal of a certiorari petition for a lack of jurisdiction and the denial of a petition on review of a nonfinal order on the merits); 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
see also 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1998145488&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_604&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_604" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Smith v. St. Vil,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 714 So.2d 603, 604 (Fla. 4th DCA 1998)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (citing 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1005170&cite=FLSTRCPR1.420&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Florida Rule of Civil Procedure 1.420(b)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 and stating that a dismissal for lack of jurisdiction is not on the merits). Although the certiorari order denied rather than dismissed the first-tier petition, the order clearly determined that the circuit court was without jurisdiction to decide the petition. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1995156392&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_649&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_649" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Parkway Bank,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 658 So.2d at 649 n. 3
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (noting that because the simple denial of a petition for certiorari has no res judicata effect, 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u8220\'3fthere is little harm in denying a writ that, technically, should be dismissed\u8221\'3f).
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F112038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[11]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F122038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[12]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Here, the circuit court explained in its certiorari order that Neapolitan was \u8220\'3fchallenging a determination made by the City Planner that awarded a parking 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_3926_592_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_3926_592_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*592
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 credit of 76 parking spaces.\u8221\'3f The circuit court stated that it first had to \u8220\'3faddress the threshhold issue of whether this Court has jurisdiction to review the City Planner\rquote s determination.\u8221\'3f The circuit court can conduct certiorari review of \u8220\'3forders of local agencies and boards that are quasi-judicial and not subject to direct review under the Administrative Procedure Act.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2023210110&pubNum=0003926&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_3926_242&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_3926_242" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Lee Cty. v. Harsh,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 44 So.3d 239, 242 (Fla. 2d DCA 2010)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. A decision is quasi-judicial, rather than executive, when notice and a hearing are required and the administrative agency\rquote s judgment depends on evidence and argument from the hearing. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Id.; 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2018160455&pubNum=0003926&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_3926_1247&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_3926_1247" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
City of St. Pete Beach v. Sowa,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 4 So.3d 1245, 1247 (Fla. 2d DCA 2009)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F132038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[13]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Certiorari review of an agency\rquote s executive decision is inappropriate because \u8220\'3fwhen an executive makes a decision without conducting a hearing, there is nothing for the circuit court to review.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2023210110&pubNum=0003926&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_3926_242&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_3926_242" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Harsh,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 44 So.3d at 242
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (quoting 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2018160455&pubNum=0003926&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_3926_1247&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_3926_1247" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Sowa,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 4 So.3d at 1247
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
). Rather, \u8220\'3f[w]hen an administrative official or agency acts in an executive or legislative capacity, the proper method of attack on the official\rquote s or agency\rquote s action \u8216\'3fis a suit in circuit court for declaratory or injunctive relief on grounds that the action taken is arbitrary, capricious, confiscatory, or violative of constitutional guarantees.\u8217\'3f \u8221\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2018160455&pubNum=0003926&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_3926_1247&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_3926_1247" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Sowa,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 4 So.3d at 1247
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (quoting 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=Ib58628050d3b11d99830b5efa1ded32a&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1976120182&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_654&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_654" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Bd. of Cty. Comm\rquote rs of Hillsborough Cty. v. Casa Dev. Ltd., II,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 332 So.2d 651, 654 (Fla. 2d DCA 1976)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
).
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The circuit court determined that the challenged decision in the September 2, 2011, letter from the Planning Director \u8220\'3fwould seem to be an instance where \u8216\'3fevidence of factual findings was in a letter stating a conclusion\u8217\'3f \u8221\'3f and thus \u8220\'3fdoes not qualify as a quasi-judicial agency decision reviewable by petition for writ of certiorari.\u8221\'3f The circuit court expressly found that it did not have jurisdiction and denied the petition. The finding essential to the circuit court\rquote s decision was that the Planning Director\rquote s decision was not quasi-judicial in nature.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
This court\rquote s per curiam denial of certiorari relief in the second-tier certiorari also was not a determination on the merits. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I1d1ec5d40c6011d9bc18e8274af85244&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2004087242&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_1254&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_1254" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Topps,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 865 So.2d at 1254
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (holding that \u8220\'3funelaborated denials entered in connection with all extraordinary writ petitions filed in any Florida court shall not be considered decisions on the merits which would bar the litigant from presenting the same or a substantially similar issue on appeal or by a subsequent writ petition, or by other means, in the same or a different Florida Court\u8221\'3f).
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Therefore, neither the circuit court nor this court decided Neapolitan\rquote s claim on the merits in the previous certiorari proceedings or determined an issue of fact or law regarding the claim raised here that the Planning Director\rquote s determination of parking credits was ultra vires and void. Accordingly, the principles of res judicata and collateral estoppel do not bar Neapolitan\rquote s claim in the current action.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F142038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[14]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F152038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[15]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The City further argues that Neapolitan has violated the prohibition against splitting causes of action. The City contends that Neapolitan should have brought its claims for declaratory and injunctive relief with its earlier certiorari petition. \u8220\'3fThe rule against splitting causes of action is \u8216\'3fan aspect of the doctrine of res judicata.\u8217\'3f
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 \u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=If5ed5757649411d9896bc143483b2851&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
