[16]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Olde Naples also argues that the doctrine of separation of powers bars the amended complaint because it attempts to challenge an executive act of the City. In doing so, Olde Naples relies upon 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
