{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F172038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[17]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F182038189609_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf37 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[18]
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In this declaratory judgment action, Neapolitan is not requesting that the City perform some discretionary act. Rather, Neapolitan has alleged that the Planning Director engaged in an ultra vires act. A municipality \u8220\'3fengages in an \u8216\'3fultra vires\rquote  act when it lacks the authority to take the action under statute or its own governing laws.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2018968508&pubNum=0003926&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_3926_191&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_3926_191" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Liberty Counsel v. Fla. Bar Bd. of Governors,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 12 So.3d 183, 191\u8211\'3f92 (Fla.2009)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Declaratory judgment actions regarding ultra vires acts are recognized as to private actors and as to local governments. 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1984105057&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_166&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_166" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Beau Monde, Inc. v. Bramson,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 446 So.2d 164, 166\u8211\'3f67 (Fla. 2d DCA 1984)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (affirming declaratory judgment when condominium association\rquote s attempted actions were ultra vires and void); 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2002194535&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_505&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_505" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Nat\rquote l Rifle Ass\rquote n of Am., Inc. v. City of S. Miami,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 812 So.2d 504, 505\u8211\'3f06 (Fla. 3d DCA 2002)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (determining that declaratory judgment action was not premature which alleged that a city\rquote s ordinance was ultra vires and void because it was expressly preempted by state law); 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I628f1ff00cf811d99830b5efa1ded32a&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=ab8035a5c4a941129019195e50064b51&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
