{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2000645750&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I28b869c3c85411e5a795ac035416da91&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_1249&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_1249" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Town of Lauderdale\u8211\'3fby\u8211\'3fthe\u8211\'3fSea v. Meretsky,
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 773 So.2d 1245, 1249 (Fla. 4th DCA 2000)
}}}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (reversing declaratory judgment in favor of landowners regarding a wall built on a public right-of-way when \u8220\'3fthe Town Commission authorized an act contrary to its own ordinances and, therefore, its approval was ultra vires and void\u8221\'3f; remanding to enter final judgment on Town\rquote s counterclaim seeking declaratory and injunctive relief to require landowners to remove wall from the right-of-way).
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Because Neapolitan has alleged ultra vires acts, Olde Naples\rquote  reliance on 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Detournay
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 and argument that the doctrine of separation of powers precludes Neapolitan\rquote s suit has no merit.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Therefore, we reject the alternative theories of res judicata, collateral estoppel, splitting a cause of action, and separation of powers. We reverse the dismissal of Neapolitan\rquote s amended complaint and remand for further proceedings.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Reversed and remanded.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
}
